com.basho.riak.client.api.commands.kv

Class FetchValue.Option<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.basho.riak.client.api.commands.RiakOption<T>
      • com.basho.riak.client.api.commands.kv.FetchValue.Option<T>
  • Enclosing class:
    FetchValue

    public static final class FetchValue.Option<T>
extends RiakOption<T>
    Options for controlling how Riak performs the fetch operation.

    These options can be supplied to the FetchValue.Builder to change how Riak performs the operation. These override the defaults provided by the bucket.

    Since:
    2.0
    Author:
    Dave Rusek

    • Field Detail

      • R

        public static final FetchValue.Option<Quorum> R
        Read Quorum. How many replicas need to agree when fetching the object.

      • PR

        public static final FetchValue.Option<Quorum> PR
        Primary Read Quorum. How many primary replicas need to be available when retrieving the object.

      • BASIC_QUORUM

        public static final FetchValue.Option<Boolean> BASIC_QUORUM
        Basic Quorum. Whether to return early in some failure cases (eg. when r=1 and you get 2 errors and a success basic_quorum=true would return an error)

      • NOTFOUND_OK

        public static final FetchValue.Option<Boolean> NOTFOUND_OK
        Not Found OK. Whether to treat notfounds as successful reads for the purposes of R

      • IF_MODIFIED

        public static final FetchValue.Option<VClock> IF_MODIFIED
        If Modified. When a vector clock is supplied with this option, only return the object if the vector clocks don't match.

      • HEAD

        public static final FetchValue.Option<Boolean> HEAD
        Head. return the object with the value(s) set as empty. This allows you to get the meta data without a potentially large value. Analogous to an HTTP HEAD request.

      • DELETED_VCLOCK

        public static final FetchValue.Option<Boolean> DELETED_VCLOCK
        Deleted VClock. By default single tombstones are not returned by a fetch operations. This will return a Tombstone if it is present.

      • TIMEOUT

        public static final FetchValue.Option<Integer> TIMEOUT
        Timeout. Sets the server-side timeout for this operation. The default in Riak is 60 seconds.

      • SLOPPY_QUORUM

        public static final FetchValue.Option<Boolean> SLOPPY_QUORUM

        public static final FetchValue.Option<Integer> N_VAL
